First, I must apologize for being wrong on it happening on all files. I tested number of files and all had the issue, but today I was also able to create a file without the issue, so it might be more tricky.

Attaching a sample file with a problem. Code to repro the issue:
```js
let workbook = new Workbook();
await workbook.xlsx.readFile(fileName);
workbook.eachSheet((sheet) => {
    sheet.eachRow((row, rowNumber) => {
        row.eachCell((cell, cellNumber) => {
            console.log(rowNumber, cellNumber, cell.alignment?.wrapText);
        });
    });
});
```
Outputs:
```
1 1 true
2 1 true
```
1 1 is expected not to be true.

[problem.xlsx](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/files/7587378/problem.xlsx)

@PRR24 
If you install exceljs from NPM, I can reproduce your problem.
If you clone the exceljs repository, this error does not exist (I wrote the test), so I think the `wrapText` problem will be solved when publishing exceljs again.

